The advertisement must air during designated commercial breaks or have dedicated commercial time. Venue signage, field graphics, or set decorations visible without dedicated commercial time do not qualify. Platform-specific ads not in the primary broadcast feed, regional ads when national broadcast is specified, and ads outside the official broadcast window do not count. Parent company ads without specific brand identification do not qualify unless the brand refers to the parent company itself. If the event is cancelled, postponed beyond the date, or experiences complete broadcast failure, the market resolves to No unless already satisfied.
early_close_condition: This market will close and expire early if the qualifying advertisement airs.

title: Will Goodbye be the #1 song on the Billboard Hot 100 charts this week?

rules_primary: If Goodbye is the #1 song on the Billboard Hot 100 charts for Sep 13, 2025 then the market resolves to Yes.
rules_secondary:

Any references to "Billboard", the "Hot 100," or any other associated marks are descriptive only, and do not indicate an endorsement of this product or any affiliation between Billboard and Kalshi.**The Billboard Hot 100 measures music consumption from a Friday to Thursday. This is released as the chart for the Saturday following Thursday (in this case, Sep 13, 2025).

Clarification 7/18/23: In the past, this market has used <date> to refer to the date at the end of the tracking week (the week in which Billboard records music consumption to be eligible for the Hot 100), a Thursday. In the future, the <date> in the Rulebook and the date listed in the short market rules on the market page will refer to the date that a given Billboard chart is dated for, as the Instructions in the market rules model. This is the second Saturday following the end of the tracking week. For example, today's new market will cover music consumption ending Thursday, July 20. The chart will be released on Tuesday, July 25. it will have a <date> corresponding to Saturday, July 29, 2023.

title: Will Shadeur Sanders be QB2 for Cleveland in Week 1?
rules_primary: If Shadeur Sanders is officially designated as Cleveland's QB2 for Week 1 of the NFL season, then the market resolves to Yes.
rules_secondary: Position designation is determined by the official depth chart published by the team for the specified week. If no official depth chart is available, the designation comes from official team communications (injury reports, press releases). For bye weeks, the market uses the last available depth chart before the bye. If the player is injured but still officially listed at the position, the market resolves to Yes. For postseason weeks, if the team is eliminated before that week, the market resolves to No. Practice squad and inactive players do not qualify unless officially promoted to the active roster at the specified position.
early_close_condition: This market will close and expire early if the official depth chart is released.
